olivia|2021 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A]]\n|date       = TBA\n|time       =\n|team1      = {{fb-rt|BOL}}\n|score      =\n|report     =\n|team2      = {{fb|ARG}}\n|goals1     =\n|goals2     =\n|stadium    = [[Estadio Ciudad de La Plata]]\n|location   = [[La Plata]], [[Argentina]]\n|attendance =\n|referee    =\n|result     =\n}}\n\n==Players==\n{{See also|:Category:Argentina international footballers|l1=Argentina international footballers}}\n\n===Current squad===\nThe following players were selected for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] on 27 and 31 March 2020, respectively. A complementary list including [[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] players will be released at a further date.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/lista-de-convocados-de-la-seleccion-mayor|title=  Lista de convocados del f\u00fatbol exterior para la Selecci\u00f3n Mayor |work=AFA|date=10 March 2020|accessdate=10 March 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March 2020, the [[FIFA]] announced that the matches originally scheduled to take place during the international window of 23-31 March 2020 are postponed to later dates. Details of the postponed matches will be discussed and announced soon.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/update-on-upcoming-fifa-world-cup-qualifiers-in-south-america|title=Update on upcoming FIFA World Cup qualifiers in South America|date=12 March 2020|website=FIFA.com|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n<br>'''Caps and goals correct as of:''' ''18 November 2019, after the match against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].\n\n{{nat fs g start|background=#0B0B3F|color=#ffffff}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=|pos=GK|name=[[Juan Musso]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1994|5|6}}|caps=1|goals=0|club=[[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]|clubnat=ITA}}\n{{nat fs break|background=#0B0B3F}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=|pos=DF|